HEADWORD: Sectionalize
<hw>Sec"tion*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To divide
according to geographical sections or local interests.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The principal results of the struggle were to
<qex>sectionalize</qex> parties.</q> <rj><qau>Nicolay & Hay (Life of
Lincoln).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sectionally</ent>⟦br⟧
